29/04/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- A man armed with a hunting rifle wounded at least 27 people Thursday (April 28th) after opening fire during an election meeting at a coffeehouse in the southern town of Samandag. Two of the wounded are in critical condition. Among the injured is opposition Republican People's Party candidate Refik Eryilmaz, who was campaigning for the June parliamentary elections. Police are searching for the gunman. (Anadolu news agency, Hurriyet, Tanjug, Press TV - 28/04/11)
